Salisbury Ground Beef
  --Laurel Rudolph

1 tbsp canola oil
1 lb 90/10 lean ground beef
1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped (~1 c)
3 large cloves garlic, finely chopped
4 tbsp unsalted butter
8 oz package sliced cremini mushrooms 
1/4 c ap flour
3 c beef broth
2 tbsp Worcestershire sauce
2 tsp Dijon mustard
1 tsp chopped fresh thyme, plus leaves for garnish  
1/2 tsp freshly ground black pepper
1-2 tsp kosher salt
12 oz pasta (like pappardelle), cooked according to package directions

Heat the oil in a large, deep-sided skillet over medium-high. Add the beef, onion, and garlic. Cook, stirring often and breaking up the beef with a wooden spoon, until the beef is browned, 4-5 min. Do not drain the beef. Transfer to a medium heatproof bowl. Without wiping the skillet clean, add the butter and heat over medium-high until melted. Add the mushrooms. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and tender, 6-8 min. Reduce the heat to medium. Add the flour and cook, stirring constantly, until lightly browned, ~2 min. Gradually whisk in the beef broth until smooth. Stir in the reserved beef mixture, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, thyme, and pepper. Bring to a simmer over medium heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the flavors meld and the sauce thickens, 5-7 min. Taste, adding salt as needed. Remove from the heat. Garnish with fresh thyme leaves and serve over the cooked pasta. 

 
Note: can serve with rice, potatoes, etc in place of pasta
